##############################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("Numeric");

$num = random(110,990,10);
$p1=random(2,9,1);
$p2=$p1/10;
$p3=$p1/100;
$d1=$p1/100;
$d2=$p2/100;
$d3=$p3/100;
$ans1 = $d1*$num;
$ans2 = $d2*$num;
$ans3 = $d3*$num;

Context("LimitedNumeric");
$ans1 = Compute($ans1);
$ans2 = Compute($ans2);
$ans3 = Compute($ans3);

##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Fill in the blanks:

a)    [_______]{$ans1} is [` [$p1]% `] of [` [$num] `]? 

b)    [_______]{$ans2} is [` [$p2]% `] of [` [$num] `]? 

c)    [_______]{$ans3} is [` [$p3]% `] of [` [$num] `]? 

END_PGML

##############################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

This translation from English to math may help you remember the percentage formula.

    [` 2 \text{ is } 50% \text{ of } 4 \Longleftrightarrow 2 = 0.5 \cdot 4 `]

a)  What is [` [$p1]% `] of [` [$num] `]? 

    [`` 
        \begin{aligned}
        x  & = [$d1] \cdot [$num] \\
         & = [$ans1] 
         \end{aligned}
         ``]

b)  What is [` [$p2]% `] of [` [$num] `]? 

    [`` 
        \begin{aligned} 
        x & = [$d2] \cdot [$num] \\
         & = [$ans2] 
         \end{aligned}
         ``]

c)  What is [` [$p3]% `] of [` [$num] `]? 

    [`` 
        \begin{aligned}
            x  & = [$d3] \cdot [$num] \\
             & = [$ans3] 
             \end{aligned}
             ``]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();


